# 10. Constraints

Potential project constraints include:

### Technical

- Real-time inference latency
- Camera quality
- Lighting conditions
- Occlusion during exercises
- Multiple food detection

### Data

- Limited Indian food datasets
- Exercise quality datasets
- Portion estimation datasets

### Hardware

- GPU requirements
- Memory usage
- Cloud inference cost

### Development

- Large project scope
- Model optimization
- Deployment complexity

---

# 11. Key Decisions

- Adopt a modular AI architecture instead of a monolithic system.
- Use Computer Vision to eliminate manual meal logging.
- Use Deep Learning for image understanding tasks.
- Integrate Large Language Models for conversational coaching.
- Design the system to support future AI modules without major architectural changes.

---

# 12. Trade-offs

| Decision | Benefit | Trade-off |
|----------|---------|-----------|
| Deep Learning | High accuracy | Higher computational cost |
| Real-time Pose Estimation | Better coaching | Increased inference latency |
| Modular Architecture | Scalability | Higher implementation complexity |
| AI Personalization | Better user experience | Requires more user data |

